{{for|the professional golfer|Jason Schultz (golfer)}} {{Infobox state representative |name = Jason Schultz |image = Jason Schultz - Official Portrait - 84th GA.jpg |image_size = 150px |state_senate1 = Iowa |district1 = [[Iowa Senate, District 9|9th]] |term_start1 = January 12, 2015 |term_end1 = |predecessor1 = [[Nancy Boettger]] |successor1 = |state_house2 = Iowa |district2 = 18th |term_start2 = January 12, 2009 |term_end2 = January 11, 2015 |predecessor2 = [[Clarence Hoffman]] |successor2 = [[Steven Holt]] |prior_term2 = 55th (2009–2013) |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1972|11|27}} |birth_place = |party = [[Republican Party of Iowa|Republican]] |spouse = Amy |children = Josie and Camryn |residence = [[Schleswig, Iowa]] |alma_mater = |occupation = |profession = Farmer, insurance adjuster |website = [https://www.legis.iowa.gov/Legislators/legislatorAllYears.aspx?PID=7507 Schultz' Website]}}
'''Jason M. Schultz''' (born November 27, 1972) is the Iowa State Senator from the [[Iowa Senate, District 9|9th District]]. A [[Republican Party of Iowa|Republican]], he served in the [[Iowa House of Representatives]] from 2009 to 2015. He lives in [[Schleswig, Iowa|Schleswig]], [[Crawford County, Iowa|Crawford County]].
Schultz worked as an [[insurance adjuster]] at Farmers Mutual Insurance Association in Schleswig and has farmed near Schleswig with his father DeWayne Schultz. For 13 years Schultz served as a volunteer firefighter, and served seven years in the [[Iowa National Guard]]. He is a retiring member of the Horn Memorial Hospital Foundation in the fall of 2007. In 2011 he endorsed Republican Presidential Candidate [[Ron Paul]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2011/07/25/paul-gets-big-endorsement-ahead-of-crucial-iowa-contest/ |work=CNN |title=Paul gets big endorsement ahead of crucial Iowa contest |date=July 25, 2011}}</ref> In 2015 he endorsed Presidential Candidate [[Ted Cruz]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://qctimes.com/news/local/government-and-politics/elections/cruz-points-to-support-in-iowa/article_aea7dd18-7753-5a2b-a3b9-e86e7740539e.html|title=Cruz points to support in Iowa|last=Tibbetts|first=Ed|work=The Quad-City Times|access-date=2017-11-04|language=en}}</ref>
{{As of|January 2013}}, Schultz serves on several committees in the Iowa House – the Economic Growth, Environmental Protection, and Labor committees. He also serves as the chair of the Local Government committee and as a member of the Administration and Regulation Appropriations Subcommittee.
As of January 2017, Schultz serves as the Chair of the Labor and Business Relations committee, and a member of the Judiciary, State Government, and Ways and Means committees.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.iowasenaterepublicans.com/senators/jason-schultz/|title=Jason Schultz|date=2015-01-12|work=Iowa Senate Republicans|access-date=2017-11-04|language=en-US}}</ref>
